    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The only account of this meeting that has been found is in <persName
                        corresp="#p_AHH1">Arnold</persName>, <ref target="#pg_473">p. 473</ref>,
                    which indicates that <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">Marshall</persName> took a poll
                    of the opinion of officers present as to when each of them thought the war with
                    Germany would be ended. The place of the meeting is not given; the time of the
                    meeting is inferred from <persName corresp="#p_AHH1">Arnold</persName>’s account
                    and from the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_660">p.
                        660</ref>.</p>
                <p>TUESDAY, DECEMBER 7, 1943<note n="1" xml:id="d458fn1">For a post-Conference
                        report of a <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">Steinhardt</persName>-<persName
                            corresp="#p_VAY1">Vyshinsky</persName> conversation and an <persName
                            corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_VAY1"
                            >Vyshinsky</persName> conversation at Cairo after <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> had departed, <hi rend="italic"
                            >see post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_858">pp. 858</ref>–<ref
                            target="#pg_859">859</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
